Symptoms:
- Settings reset after container restart
- Data disappears
- Have to reconfigure service each time
- “First-time setup” wizard appears again

Diagnosis:
docker inspect [container] | grep -A 10 Mounts
ls -la /opt/docker/[service]/
cat docker-compose.yml | grep -A 10 [service]

Common Causes:
- Volume not mounted (data stored in container, lost on restart)
- Wrong volume path in docker-compose.yml
- Volume deleted accidentally
- Bind mount pointing to non-existent directory

Solutions:

Check docker-compose.yml has volumes:
nano /opt/docker/docker-compose.yml

# Should have:

  services:\\
    [service]:\\
      volumes:\\
        - ./[service]-data:/data  # or similar persistent path\\


If missing volume:
# Stop container
docker compose down [service]

# Add volume to docker-compose.yml
# Create directory
mkdir -p /opt/docker/[service]-data

# Restart
docker compose up -d [service]
# Note: Previous config is lost, must reconfigure

If wrong path:
# Fix path in docker-compose.yml
# Restart container
docker compose down [service]
docker compose up -d [service]

Prevention:
- Always define volumes in docker-compose.yml
- Test restart before considering service “deployed”
- Document data locations in service catalog
